I have ordered from numerous Happy Wok's in the area for years. Always been a happy customer. Tonight I ordered from this particular location for the first time. I waited over an hour then recieved a phone call from driver saying they couldn't find my house. I tried to explain to her where my home was located numerous times and in the middle of me talking to her she would just hang up on me. Her daughter was in the background yelling and asking questions. When they finally arrived at my home my drinks had spilled all over the food and everything was soaked. My husband then said something about it and her daughter starts screaming out the passenger side of the car cussing us out. He handed her the food back and took back the money. I then called the restaurant to inform them on their employees behavior and as soon as I gave my address was hung up on. UNBELIEVABLE SERVICE AND TREATMENT! Wouldn't waste my time.

I've been a customer of Happy Wok for over 20 years and have visited their numerous restaurants in the area. Today, my family was seeing a show at the BMO and we were waiting outside for our friends to arrive who had our tickets. My 5 year old daughter had to go to the bathroom and my wife walked her into your restaurant to use the bathroom.  An employee told them they couldn't use it unless they bought something.  After all the money I've spent over the years at your area restaurants, your employees are going to pull this.  I will never spend another dime of my money at any Happy Wok restaurants ever again.

I was charged 7 and some change more than the actual cost of my order. The cashier seemed to also be the cook because he was  the only person there.  My chicken in the fried rice was very undercooked. Even the fortune cookie was stale.  Very bad experience.

I order lunch there in February 1, 2018. Egg drop soup, crab Rangoon and chicken fried rice. I was eating the chicken fried rice and got maybe a third into it and then I got the biggest, nastiest spoiled tasting bite. I wanted to throw up. The food was definitely spoiled. I called the restaurant to give them the heads up as to what happened. The girl on the phone just wanted to argue with me. I said I’m not trying to get free food and I don’t know what happened, I’m just giving you the heads up. She still wanted to argue with me telling me they don’t do that. I have worked around food long enough to know if something is spoiled. It’s like the yummy fresh stuff was on top and the “leftovers” were on the bottom. Won’t go there again.

I will not eat here ever again. Egg Rolls were dry and stale and the vegetables were past where they should have been served. The store itself is filthy and smells of old grease along with boxes and jink piled up every where. It was a horrible experience.
Only thing good here is that the food is hot and cheap. You get what you pay for.  That's a shame too cuz I actually like Happy Wok.

If I could rate this place 0 stars, I would. This place is absolutely disgusting and should not share the name Happy Wok. We asked for our fried rice combo and our shrimp lo mein to be extra spicy and there wasn't a single flake of spice in either. They also only sent us one cup of hot sauce to be shared between 6 people. The rice looked and tasted like it came out of a box. The lo mein noodles were pasty and stuck together like they used yesterdays leftovers. We ordered extra shrimp, which were smaller than a nickel, and there was barely any shrimp. I could only imagine had we not ordered extra shrimp. I don’t know what the chicken was made out of but it was not chicken. It had a completely different taste and texture, absolutely disgusting. If you want good Happy Wok go to the one on 11th St or the one on E. State. DO NOT go to this place unless you want to be disgusted and grossed out when you get your food.
Great food.

I'm very surprised to see that this place has any reviews above one star.  I went inside and the place smelled rancid (this should have been my first clue and it's really on me for not turning around and walking out).  When I got my food, the fried rice and sweet and sour pork had clearly been cooked in very, very old grease.  And I'm guessing the foul odor might have come from having a grease trap that wasn't cleaned in quite a while.  Anyhow, I am the furthest thing from a picky eater there is and the taste of the food is a secondary concern here to how incredibly unsanitary it is to cook using re-used grease.  I'm not trying to be glib here but I would steer clear of this place for the sake of your health.
This place sucks, worst service of my life

I'd rather eat day old gas station sushi off the the bathroom floor covered in chunky UTI piss then eat here again. Ordered beef and broccoli and I don't even think they gave me broccoli. It was mushy yet crunchy and was yellow... Then the sauce was probably juiced from the bottom of their garbage bag. Like a frothy mix of beef sauce and sweet n sour sauce. Then I asked for fried rice and got some weird yellow rice with nothing in it but was still charged for the fried rice. Worst chineese food bullshit experience ever...

I've ate there a couple of times.  First time I ate a year ago, it was good.   I would have rated it a 4.  Then I did order a take out, it was good.  Then last couple months ago I ate there, it was okay, but the fountain pop was not the greatest.  So I ate there a couple days ago.  It was the worst.  They've left their door open to let fresh air in, which is not a problem, but I had to deal with someone smoking outside, not cool!  I ordered fried rice, but it looked like it was white rice dyed into to brown it up instead of it being really fried.  The pop from the fountain still wasn't that great tasting, not sure if it's because maybe old fountain syrup or did not clean anything for a while.  The orange chicken was alright.  But what really turned me off, was the stale fortune cookies to top it all off.  After this, I'm not coming back to this one.  Maybe other Happy Woks, but not this one.

Ordered A FAMILY SIZE Shrimp Fried Rice and a FAMILY SIZE Orange Chicken and 4 Beef Egg Rolls and had a coupon for a free family size Chicken Fried Rice over  the phone for pick-up she said okay that will be 21.83. I got to the restaurant paid the 21.83 got to the car and seen there wasn't any soy sauce in the bag. I asked my little sister to go inside and ask for some more. She gave her TWO, so I went in and asked for more since I got FAMILY SIZE meals.. After going back and forth the lady finally gave me about 10 more. We got all the way home I realized all the containers were their SMALLEST SIZES yet she charged me for FAMILY SIZES, I was going to just look over it but I ate ONE egg roll and tasted the rice. The rice wasn't done and had no taste to it whatsoever, the "beef egg roll" had god knows what in it but it DEF wasn't beef! Called the lady back and she basically argued with me for 10 minutes then finally said I could bring the food back in. Brought it back, and she looked in each box seen there was one eggroll missing and instead of giving my whole 21.83 back for her being rude and getting my order wrong she gave me 18.00 and said she HAD to charge me for eating the egg roll!?!?!? ummmm. the egg rolls are ONE DOLLAR AND NINETEEN CENTS NOT THREE DOLLARS!!!!  NEVER GOING BACK TO THAT LOCATION AGAIN!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
